# Agent run input protocol

When a dispatched Claude task on a paired Mac needs a human decision mid-run, use the WebSocket protocol — not database columns.

## Marker (required in model output)

```
[[AWAITING_INPUT]]
<single clear question on the next line>
```

## Server behavior

- Pending input lives in `dispatchAgentRunInputRegistry` (in-memory) until answered or the run completes.
- `agent_runs.status` stays `running`; job history does not get a separate paused status.
- Every `command.claude.run` prompt is wrapped with `wrapPromptWithAgentRunInputGuardrails()` before dispatch.

## Local Mac behavior

- `~/.agent-witch/profiles/<email>/pending-run-inputs.json` stores paused sessions across agent restarts.
- On reconnect, agent-witch replays `command.claude.input_required` to the server.

## Browser behavior

- `DispatchApprovalListener` also shows `AgentRunInputModal` when `command.claude.input_required` arrives on the dashboard socket.
- Answers are sent with `command.claude.input_respond` (not REST).

